Just the config. To make the complete-model .pth the loader expects, one shell paste:
python

python -c "
import sys, torch
sys.path.insert(0, 'model_sources/MobileNetV2/src/pytorch/pytorch-ssd')
from vision.ssd.mobilenet_v2_ssd_lite import create_mobilenetv2_ssd_lite
m = create_mobilenetv2_ssd_lite(num_classes=21, is_test=True)
m.load_state_dict(torch.load(
    'model_sources/MobileNetV2/weights/mb2-ssd-lite-mp-0_686.pth',
    map_location='cpu', weights_only=False), strict=True)
m.eval()
torch.save(m, 'model_sources/MobileNetV2/weights/mb2_ssd_lite_complete.pth')
print('done')
"

Run that once from project root. Then the toolkit's torch.load(model_path, weights_only=False) gets a complete SSD object; source_path puts pytorch-ssd/ on sys.path so pickle resolves vision.ssd.ssd.SSD. No new classes anywhere.
